The paper is about evaluating cross-media similarity models for web image retrieval, which is a task related to information retrieval (IR) and computer vision (CV). The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques to categorize queries, which falls under computational linguistics (CL). The experiments involve large-scale datasets, which could be considered as multimedia (MM) research. Finally, the paper proposes a simple method for text-to-image retrieval, which could be seen as a machine learning (LG) approach.
